  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "A fine-grained sentiment analysis is the aspect-based sentiment analysis (ABSA) which is the sentiment classification of the aspect of a product.",
    "For ABSA, TM is one of the techniques used to extract the aspect/topics.",
    "For example, Liu et al. (2022) used LDA to extract trending topics from Sina Weibo dataset and thereafter mined the sentiment towards the topics using public opinion cellular automata.",
    "Our literature review synthesis revealed that many studies used LDA to extract the topics (Omranian et al. 2023) and then mined the sentiment towards the topics using lexicon-based approach (Nowacki and Niezgoda 2023; Sun et al. 2016; Xianghua et al. 2013).",
    "Similarly, few studies proposed variants of LDA for topic-sentiment analysis."
  ],
